#PoGo
Playing around with OpenCV and JSON files to make a spreadsheet for Pokemon Go.

## Requirements
Software requirements and install steps for MacOS.

```
brew install tesseract --HEAD


pip3 install pytesseract
pip3 install opencv-python
pip3 install imutils
```

## Use
Photos must be 1125 × 2436 and `*.PNG` format.

1. Upload regular screenshot to `\dataA`
2. Upload IV screenshot to `dataB`
3. Run `main.py` and edit lines accordingly
```
# Log data -> Filename, printFlag, csvFlag
G.logDataA('dataA.csv', True, True)
G.logDataB('dataB.csv', True, True)
```
4. Retrieve the most up to date GAME_MASTER.json file: `wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pokemongo-dev-contrib/pokemongo-game-master/master/versions/latest/GAME_MASTER.json`
5. To do... 


